───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
CONTEXT
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
The MRR workflow allows users to upload an Excel file containing
their requisition. The Excel is a single sheet where:
- Each row represents one line item.
- Header-level fields (Project Number, Requisition Type, Need By
  Date, Description, Comments) repeat identically on every row.
- Item-level fields (Item Name, Requested Quantity, Return Date)
  vary per row.

The validator must:
1. Validate the structure (required columns present, no extra junk).
2. Validate consistency (header fields identical across rows).
3. Validate field values (correct format, allowed values).
4. Resolve user-friendly inputs (project number → PROJECTID, item
   name → ITEMID, etc.) using the data-resolution layer built in
   Task 4.5.
5. Return EITHER a fully-resolved data structure ready for DB insert,
   OR a list of friendly error messages.

The resolver does NOT write to the database. The workflow (Task 4.7)
will take the validated structure and do the DB inserts.

A few earlier Task 4.5 resolver functions live in oracle_queries.py
because we initially planned Oracle. The Oracle environment is not
yet ready; MariaDB will host these tables instead. As part of this
task, MOVE the Oracle-dependent resolvers to mariadb_queries.py and
update implementations to use MariaDB SessionLocal.

